President Trump gave a speech at the St. Charles Convention Center in Missouri, where he discussed the importance of passing tax cuts for American families and small businesses. He thanked Governor Greitens and Attorney General Hawley for their support and also praised Missouri's congressional delegation. The President highlighted the need to cut taxes in order to make the US more competitive globally and to bring back jobs that have been lost to other countries. He emphasized the positive impact that tax cuts would have on the American economy, including job creation and higher wages. President Trump also mentioned his administration's efforts to rebuild the military and secure the country's borders. He urged Congress to pass the tax cut plan and promised to sign it into law. The President concluded his speech by saying that passing tax cuts would be a great Christmas present for the American people and that it would be done with a big, beautiful tax cut.